#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn11.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. The First Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 10. Samuddakasutta → isayosamuddakasuttaṃ (bj) | isayo samuddakā (sambara) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn11.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Samuddakasutta "
msgstr "10. Hermits by the Ocean "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.489, sc1
msgctxt "sn11.10:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.10:1.2"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, sambahulā isayo sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā samuddatīre paṇṇakuṭīsu sammanti. "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, mendicants, several hermits who were ethical, of good character, settled in leaf huts by the ocean. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.10:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena devāsurasaṅgāmo samupabyūḷho ahosi. "
msgstr "Now at that time a battle was fought between the gods and the demons. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.10:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, tesaṃ isīnaṃ sīlavantānaṃ kalyāṇadhammānaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then the hermits thought, "

msgctxt "sn11.10:1.5"
msgid "‘dhammikā kho devā, adhammikā asurā. "
msgstr "‘The gods are principled, the demons are unprincipled. "

msgctxt "sn11.10:1.6"
msgid "Siyāpi no asurato bhayaṃ. "
msgstr "We may be at risk from the demons. "

msgctxt "sn11.10:1.7"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ sambaraṃ asurindaṃ upasaṅkamitvā abhayadakkhiṇaṃ yāceyyāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t we approach Sambara, lord of demons, and beg him for a pledge of safety.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.10:1.8"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, te isayo sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—samuddatīre paṇṇakuṭīsu antarahitā sambarassa asurindassa sammukhe pāturahesuṃ. "
msgstr "Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, those hermits vanished from those leaf huts by the ocean and reappeared in Sambara’s presence. "

msgctxt "sn11.10:1.9"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, te isayo sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā sambaraṃ asurindaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsiṃsu: "
msgstr "Then those hermits addressed Sambara in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn11.10:2.1"
msgid "‘Isayo sambaraṃ pattā, "
msgstr "‘The hermits have come to Sambara "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:2.2"
msgid "yācanti abhayadakkhiṇaṃ; "
msgstr "to beg for a pledge of safety. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:2.3"
msgid "Kāmaṅkaro hi te dātuṃ, "
msgstr "For you can give them what you wish, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:2.4"
msgid "bhayassa abhayassa vā’ti. "
msgstr "whether danger or safety.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn11.10:3.1"
msgid "‘Isīnaṃ abhayaṃ natthi, "
msgstr "‘There is no safety for hermits, "

# NOTE: I don’t think “devotees” of sakka is right, if anything he is their devotee!
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:3.2"
msgid "duṭṭhānaṃ sakkasevinaṃ; "
msgstr "the hated associates of Sakka! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:3.3"
msgid "Abhayaṃ yācamānānaṃ, "
msgstr "Though you beg me for your safety, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:3.4"
msgid "bhayameva dadāmi vo’ti. "
msgstr "I’ll only give you fear!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn11.10:4.1"
msgid "‘Abhayaṃ yācamānānaṃ, "
msgstr "‘Though we beg you for our safety, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:4.2"
msgid "bhayameva dadāsi no; "
msgstr "you give us only fear. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:4.3"
msgid "Paṭiggaṇhāma te etaṃ, "
msgstr "This is what we get from you: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:4.4"
msgid "akkhayaṃ hotu te bhayaṃ. "
msgstr "may endless peril come to you! "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn11.10:5.1"
msgid "Yādisaṃ vapate bījaṃ, "
msgstr "Whatever kind of seed you sow, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:5.2"
msgid "tādisaṃ harate phalaṃ; "
msgstr "that is the fruit you reap. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:5.3"
msgid "Kalyāṇakārī kalyāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "A doer of good gets good, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:5.4"
msgid "pāpakārī ca pāpakaṃ; "
msgstr "a doer of bad gets bad. "

# NOTE: tāta is odd here. I wonder if it’s used like a passive-aggressive “dude “or” mate”.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:5.5"
msgid "Pavuttaṃ tāta te bījaṃ, "
msgstr "You have sown your own seed, friend, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:5.6"
msgid "phalaṃ paccanubhossasī’ti. "
msgstr "now you’ll experience the fruit.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.228, pts2ed1.491, sc6
msgctxt "sn11.10:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, te isayo sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā sambaraṃ asurindaṃ abhisapitvā—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—sambarassa asurindassa sammukhe antarahitā samuddatīre paṇṇakuṭīsu pāturahesuṃ. "
msgstr "Then those hermits, having cursed Sambara, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, vanished from Sambara’s presence and reappeared in those leaf huts by the ocean. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.10:6.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sambaro asurindo tehi isīhi sīlavantehi kalyāṇadhammehi abhisapito rattiyā sudaṃ tikkhattuṃ ubbijjī”ti. "
msgstr "But after being cursed by the hermits, Sambara woke in alarm three times that night.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn11.10:6.3"
msgid "Paṭhamo vaggo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn11.10:7.1"
msgid "Suvīraṃ susīmañceva, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:7.2"
msgid "dhajaggaṃ vepacittino; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:7.3"
msgid "Subhāsitaṃ jayañceva, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:7.4"
msgid "kulāvakaṃ nadubbhiyaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:7.5"
msgid "Verocana asurindo, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:7.6"
msgid "isayo araññakañceva; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.10:7.7"
msgid "Isayo ca samuddakāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
